                            <li>Type <code>!</code> and press <strong>Tab</strong></li>
                            <li><strong>Magic!</strong> Full HTML5 boilerplate appears</li>
                        </ol>

                        <h5>Understanding the boilerplate:</h5>
                        <div class="code-block">
&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;
&lt;html lang="en"&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
    &lt;meta charset="UTF-8"&gt;
    &lt;meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"&gt;
    &lt;title&gt;Document&lt;/title&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;

&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
                        </div>

                        <h5>What each part means:</h5>
                        <ul>
                            <li><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</code> - Tells browser this is HTML5</li>
                            <li><code>&lt;html lang="en"&gt;</code> - Root element, language declaration</li>
                            <li><code>&lt;head&gt;</code> - Metadata (not visible on page)</li>
                            <li><code>&lt;meta charset="UTF-8"&gt;</code> - Character encoding</li>
                            <li><code>&lt;meta name="viewport"...&gt;</code> - Responsive design setup</li>
                            <li><code>&lt;title&gt;</code> - Page title (shows in browser tab)</li>
                            <li><code>&lt;body&gt;</code> - Visible content goes here</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

